"This lab experiment (CS268, Experiment-3) is centered on the design and implementation of Booth's multiplier, an algorithm specifically for efficient multiplication of 2's complement signed integers. Building on prior knowledge of logic gates and arithmetic, students will utilize Verilog for coding, iverilog for compilation, and gtkwave for waveform analysis. A key component of the experiment involves debugging pre-written Booth multiplier Verilog code, which is structured with distinct datapath and control path modules. Students are tasked with understanding the code's flow, identifying the specific module or submodule containing errors, explaining the nature of the bug, and subsequently rectifying it."